<GlossaryTerm id="CDR0000046213"><TermName>achlorhydria</TermName><TermPronunciation>(ay-klor-HY-dree-uh)</TermPronunciation><TermDefinition><DefinitionText>A lack of hydrochloric acid in the digestive juices in the stomach. Hydrochloric acid helps digest food.</DefinitionText><Dictionary>Cancer.gov</Dictionary><Audience>Patient</Audience></TermDefinition><MediaLink ref="CDR0000707841" type="audio/mpeg" alt="Pronunciation of dictionary term &quot;achlorhydria&quot;" language="en" id="_4"/><MediaLink ref="CDR0000707840" type="audio/mpeg" alt="Pronunciation of dictionary term &quot;aclorhidría&quot;" language="es" id="_3"/><SpanishTermName>aclorhidria</SpanishTermName><SpanishTermDefinition><DefinitionText>Falta de ácido clorhídrico en los jugos digestivos del estómago. El ácido clorhídrico ayuda a digerir los alimentos.</DefinitionText><Dictionary>Cancer.gov</Dictionary><Audience>Patient</Audience></SpanishTermDefinition></GlossaryTerm>
